org.rdkit.knime.nodes.rdkfingerprint

Interface FingerprintSettings

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultFingerprintSettings, FingerprintSettingsHeaderProperty

    public interface FingerprintSettings
    Defines fingerprint settings used to calculate fingerprints. Not all settings are used for all types of fingerprints. If a string setting is unavailable null should be returned. For numeric settings this is not possible, therefore the constant UNAVAILABLE has been introduced, which shall be used to express that a setting is not defined. The value of UNAVAILABLE may change over time, if the current value is needed in the future for a new type of settings.
    Author:
    Manuel Schwarze
